  "text": "À/À mice and wild-type (LTC 4 S +/+ ) littermate controls on a BALB/c background were originally generated as described [CITATION_1] . IL-5 transgenic BALB/c mice heterozygous for a transgene that expresses murine IL-5 under the control of human CD2 regulatory sequences [CITATION_2] were obtained courtesy of Dr. Craig Gerard (Boston Children's Hospital). Protocols used were approved by the Institutional Animal Care and Use Committee at Beth Israel Deaconess Medical Center.",
